<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Policemen Depart for Gaza Duty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Policemen Depart for Gaza Duty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2805220394 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2805220394 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning a new group of Palestinian police left 
Algeria by air. 
  In implementation of the articles of the self-rule 
agreement, 
which stipulate for the creation of a Palestinian police force 
in the two areas of Gaza and Jericho, a new group of Palestinian 
police left at dawn today by air from Laghouat military airport, 
heading for Rafah on the Egyptian-Palestinian border. 
  Brigadier-General Fodil Saidi, commander of the Fourth 
Military Zone, was at the farewell of the group. 
  This group is composed of 256 soldiers, most of them are 
young, who received training at Algerian military academies. 
  This group will enter the Palestinian territories tomorrow, 
Sunday evening, to be deployed in the city of Gaza. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

