<H3> <TI>   National Authority Meets, Discusses Action Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Authority Meets, Discusses Action Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Members To Take Oath in Homeland </H4>

<F P=102> NC2705171694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1650 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2705171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Tunis, 27 May (MENA) -- At its meeting today 
under Yasir 'Arafat's chairmanship, the Palestinian National 
Authority Council decided to have its members take the 
constitutional oath before 'Arafat on the homeland's soil. The 
Council also decided to have 'Arafat take the constitutional 
oath in the homeland before Salim al-Za'nun, alias Abu-al-Adib, 
acting chairman of the Palestine National Council, the 
Palestinian parliament. 
  This was stated by council member Dr. Samir Ghawshah 
following today's meeting. Ghawshah said that 'Arafat has 
decided to appoint Muhammad Zuhdi al-Nashashibi, member of the 
PLO Executive Committee and chief of its economic department, as 
a member to the council. He is the 20th member. 
  Ghawshah said that 'Arafat will continue his consultations 
with the various Palestinian powers to appoint five more members 
of the 25-member council. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

