<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministers for 14 National Authority Posts Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministers for 14 National Authority Posts Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2805124094 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1100 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2805124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The PLO has handed out 14 of 22 portfolios in the 
Palestinian self-rule administration in the Gaza Strip and 
Jericho area. 
  Mr. Ahmad Quray', a key player in the secret peace deal with 
Israel, was named to be in charge of economy and trade. Mr. 
Samir Ghawshah, who was given the labor and social affairs 
portfolio, said other ministers in the Palestinian National 
Authority included chief self-rule negotiator Nabil Sha'th at 
planning and economic cooperation, and PLO Executive Committee 
member Muhammad Zuhdi al- Nashashibi at finance. 
  Mr. Ghawshah said the portfolios were handed out at a 
meeting 
in Tunis last night and consultations were continuing on those 
still to be handed out. He listed the 14 so far distributed as: 
  1. Economy and Trade, Ahmad Quray', alias Abu-'Ala' 
  2. Finances, Muhammad Zuhdi al-Nashashibi 
  3. Planning and Economic Cooperation, Nabil Sha'th 
  4. Housing, Zakariya al-Agha 
  5. Communications and Post, 'Abd-al-Hafiz al-Ashhab 
  6. Education and Teaching, Yasir 'Amr 
  7. Culture and Arts, Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh 
  8. Justice, Furayh Abu-Middayn 
  9. Labor and Workers, Samir Ghawshah 
  10. Social Affairs, Intisar al-Wazir, alias Umm-Jihad 
  11. Local Government, Sa'ib 'Urayqat 
  12. Youth and Sports, 'Azmi al-Shu'aybi 
  13. Tourism and Monuments, Ilyas Furayj 
  14. Health, Riyad al-Za'nun 
  The meetings are due to resume later today. 

</TEXT>

