<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abu-Zayyad Says Israel To Compromise on Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abu-Zayyad Says Israel To Compromise on Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2705114694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 27 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2705114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian negotiator and East Jerusalem lawyer 
Ziyad Abu-Zayyad says that Palestinians naturally view East 
Jerusalem as the capital of the state they hope to establish. 
  [Begin recording] [Abu-Zayyad] East Jerusalem is a symbol 
of the Palestinian nationality, of the Arab dignity, and of the 
Islamic belief and faith. And, of course, it is viewed by us as 
our future capital. 
  [Correspondent Mark Weiss] Can you confirm that the PLO is 
engaged in efforts to continue moving national institutions to 
East Jerusalem? 
  [Abu-Zayyad] Well, I think that the issue of Jerusalem is 
supposed to be on the negotiating table in the second phase of 
the negotiations, and I believe that this thing will be 
discussed through negotiations. I don't think that the PLO will 
move its offices to Jerusalem without negotiations and without 
coordinating with the other side because at the end we need to 
find a solution for Jerusalem which will be for the satisfaction 
of all parties. 
  [Weiss] Israeli leaders, at the moment at least, insist that 
Jerusalem will remain the united capital of Israel. Do you 
believe Israel will eventually compromise on this issue? 
  [Abu-Zayyad] Well, of course yes. Of course I do, because 
anyone who wants peace he knows deep in his heart that he cannot 
have peace and have Jerusalem only under the Israeli 
sovereignty. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

