<H3> <TI>   Fatah Invites Gazan Citizens To Join Movement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Invites Gazan Citizens To Join Movement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3005082194 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 27 May p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC3005082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gaza, Jerusalem Press -- For the first time since 
its inception outside the occupied territories on 1 January 
1965, Fatah -- the Palestinian National Liberation Movement -- 
has publicly opened the door of membership to its ranks. 
  In a statement, Fatah said the need to rebuild its 
structures 
is the main reason why it is inviting the Palestinians in the 
Gaza Strip to join up. Fatah operated as a secret organization 
until the signing of the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of 
Principles on 13 September 1993. 
  The statement, which was signed by the Fatah Mobilization 
and 
Reorganization Department, announced the opening of several 
offices in the Gaza Strip to enable Palestinians to join the 
movement. 

</TEXT>

