<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Chief: Refuge Seekers Not To Be Handed Over </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2905063794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 0600 GMT 29 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2905063794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Major General Nasri Yusuf, commander of the 
Palestinian Police Force, has stated that his forces will refuse 
to hand over to Israel alleged perpetrators of operations 
against the Israeli state who seek refuge in the self-rule areas. 
  At a news conference in Gaza, he said: We will not permit 
the Israelis to come and arrest anyone in the sectors that are 
under our control. Maj. Gen. Nasri Yusuf also said that the 
Palestinian police will issue arms licenses to the self-rule 
inhabitants, but will not permit weapons to be carried on the 
streets as they should be kept at home. 

</TEXT>

