<H3> <TI>   APF Statement Says Police `Repressive Tool' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    APF Statement Says Police `Repressive Tool' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3005205094 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1630 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3005205094 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Alliance of Palestinian Forces [APF] issued a 
political statement following a recent meeting during which the 
APF discussed political and security developments in the 
Palestinian arena. The conferees examined some of the serious 
measures undertaken by the corrupt Oslo team in the context of 
the Gaza-Jericho agreement. 
  In its statement, the APF said that the suspect role 
assigned 
to the so-called Palestinian police has shown them to be a 
repressive tool in the hand of the Zionist occupation. As part 
of the practical arrangements agreed on between the Oslo team 
and the Zionist enemy, a number of those affiliated with the 
Zionist enemy agencies made statements on disarming our people 
and their militant forces and on opening prisons for our 
people's honorable strugglers. In this context, they have 
started by detaining Hani 'Abid, an Islamic Jihad member, and 
pursuing our people's strugglers who reject the Oslo agreement 
and all its appendices, chapters, and objectives. 
  The APF statement adds: We in the APF warn of the gravity of 
this dangerous behavior which will lead to detrimental results, 
sedition, and internal strife. We urge the masses of our people 
and their militant forces to firmly confront the practices of 
this team which has violated the will of our people, and its 
agencies which have been proved to be dens designed to absorb 
agents and spies linked to the Zionist enemy. 

</TEXT>

