<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Official Denies Pelletreau Claims of Rift </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Official Denies Pelletreau Claims of Rift </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3005090894 Amman AL-MAJD in Arabic 30 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN3005090894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-MAJD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on statements by Robert Pelletreau, U.S. 
assistant secretary of state for Near Eastern and South Asian 
affairs, on a rift within the Hamas Movement, Hamas official 
Muhammad Nazzal said: I defy Pelletreau to name one Hamas 
leader inside or outside the occupied territories who is working 
to divide the movement, or who has deviated from its consensus 
of rejecting participation in the Palestinian authority or in 
the self-rule farce. 
  Nazzal said that the U.S. official's statements are sheer 
fabrications and part of the false reports claiming that the 
'Arafat leadership has succeeded in gaining the support of 
several Hamas leaders in the occupied territories for the 
Palestinian Authority, thus deviating from the movement's 
constants of rejecting the capitulatory march and abiding by 
armed struggle and protracted Jihad until all the Palestinian 
national soil is liberated. 
  Pelletreau has claimed that a rift recently developed within 
Hamas in the occupied territories over participation in the 
Palestinian National Authority. 

</TEXT>

