<H3> <TI>   Government Pushes UN Censure of Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Pushes UN Censure of Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ministry Summons UNSC Ambassadors </H4>

<F P=102> NC2805133594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1300 GMT 28 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2805133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Ministry Secretary General Zafir al-Hasan 
today summoned the ambassadors of the United States, Russia, 
France, Britain, and China for consultations on Lebanon's call 
for a UN Security Council [UNSC] meeting to discuss Israel's 
kidnapping of al-Hajj Mustafa al-Dirani. 
  Al-Hasan said Lebanon's decision to request a Security 
Council meeting will not await a response by the five big 
powers. He explained that Lebanon's Permanent Representative to 
the UN Khalil Makkawi has been instructed to call for a meeting 
without specifying a date for it. 
  After the meeting, Russian Ambassador Gennadiy Ilichev said 
he will convey Lebanon's request to his government for a 
decision. U.S. Ambassador Mark Hambley denied that he knows 
anything about U.S efforts to discourage Lebanon from calling 
for a UN Security Council meeting. 

</TEXT>

