<H3> <TI>   Hizballah Vows Retribution for Kidnapping </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hizballah Vows Retribution for Kidnapping </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Nasrallah Calls For End to Talks </H4>

<F P=102> NC3005060194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0430 GMT 30 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3005060194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hizballah Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah has 
called on the Lebanese Government to withdraw from the peace 
talks in response to Israel's abduction of Mustafa al-Dirani. 
He affirmed that civilian peace is in the interest of the 
resistance, coexistence, and building a state to which all 
Lebanese aspire. 
  Al-Dirani's family yesterday appealed to the International 
Committee of the Red Cross [ICRC] to act quickly in providing 
medical assistance to him. In a memorandum submitted to the 
ICRC, al-Dirani's family held Israel responsible for the 
deterioration of his health and for preventing the Red Cross 
from visiting him. 

</TEXT>

