<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's al-'Attas Visits as Envoy for Vice President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemen's al-'Attas Visits as Envoy for Vice President </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Amir </H4>

<F P=102> LD3005122194 Kuwait Radio Kuwait in Arabic 1000 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait Radio Kuwait </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] His highness the amir of Kuwait, God safeguard 
him, today received Mr. Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, the envoy of 
'Ali Salim al-Bid, the secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist 
Party. Al-'Attas briefed his highness about the fighting and the 
development of the conflict in Yemen, and the reactions to this 
crisis at the Arab and regional level. 
  His highness, God safeguard him, was keen to express 
Kuwait's 
firm and principled stance, which calls for tackling problems 
according to the logic of national interest and by brotherly 
dialogue without the use of violence. Resorting to violence and 
the use of arms increases disputes and complicates problems. It 
would also deepen wounds, waste energy and result in destruction. 
  In this context, His highness the amir, God safeguard him, 
expressed his concern that the Yemeni conflict could have a bad 
effect on the Arab situation. This is a matter that worries all 
leaders and officials, especially as the Arab nation needs to 
close ranks and reunite to regain its dignity and influence. 
  At the end of the meeting his highness the amir affirmed 
that 
Kuwait will support all honest and beneficial efforts to stop 
the bloodshed and restore understanding and reconciliation 
between the two parts of Yemen. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

