<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] His Highness Shaykh Jabir al-Ahmad al-Sabah, the 
amir of the fraternal state of Kuwait, this afternoon received 
brother Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, the prime minister, who 
briefed him on the developments of the dispute in our country, 
the progress of the battles there, and regional and Arab 
reactions. During the meeting, Shaykh Jabir al-Ahmad al-Sabah 
expressed fraternal Kuwait's firm and consistent stand which 
calls for the settling of disputes with the logic of national 
interest and fraternal dialogue in isolation of the use of 
force. His highness stressed during his meeting with brother 
Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas that the use of force and arms would 
only exacerbate the differences and problems. Wounds would be 
deepened and strength would be lost, while destruction would 
prevail. He said Kuwait would support any sincere and useful 
effort to stem the bloodshed and restore understanding and amity 
between the two parts of Yemen. The amir of Kuwait expressed 
fear that the Yemeni conflict would have adverse effects on the 
overall Arab situation. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

