<H4>    Al-'Attas: Iraq, Sudan Aiding North </H4>

<F P=102> EA3105111794 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 2045 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA3105111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 2045 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Before his departure from the 
fraternal state of Kuwait, Prime Minister Haydar Abu-Bakr 
al-'Attas held a news conference in which he accused the Sanaa 
regime of aiming at controlling the oilfields in the Democratic 
Republic of Yemen. He pointed out that some Arab countries such 
as Iraq and Sudan are directly involved in the northern forces' 
war against our country. 
  The brother prime minister said that the northern forces' 
war 
against our country is exactly similar to Iraq's invasion of the 
fraternal state of Kuwait in 1990. In both cases there are 
misplaced ideas claiming the annexation of a part to the 
motherland. The brother prime minister confirmed that the 
objective behind the declaration of the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen was to prevent the breakup of Yemen into numerous smaller 
states. 

</TEXT>

