<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id Al Sa'id, the 
sultan of the Sultanate of Oman, received late this afternoon 
Brother Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, the chairman of the Council 
of Ministers. The OMANI NEWS AGENCY, which reported this, said 
that the talks concentrated on the current situation in the 
Yemeni arena, and the means by which a solution could be found 
to save the Yemeni people from the woes of the ongoing war and 
achieve peace and stability for the Yemeni people. 
  During the meeting Sultan Qabus expressed his interest in an 
end to the fighting, so that the shedding of the blood of the 
brothers in Yemen could stop and the stability of Yemen and its 
security could be maintained and preserved. He stressed the 
necessity of the disputing parties returning to dialogue, 
instead of fighting among themselves, to achieve the aspirations 
of the Yemeni people for stability and development. 
  Brother Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas arrived in Muscat this 
afternoon for a visit to the Sultanate of Oman. During this 
visit he will be holding talks with Omani officials about the 
ongoing situation in Yemen, within the framework of the efforts 
and concern of the fraternal Sultanate of Oman, to stop the war 
and stop the bloodletting of the Yemeni people. On arrival at 
the Sib airport he was received by al-Sayyid Bin-Hamad 
Bin-Su'ud, minister of the sultan's palace, and Yusuf Bin-'Alawi 
Bin-'Abdallah, the Omani minister of state for foreign affairs. 

</TEXT>

