<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Said To Call al-Bid With Cease-Fire Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Said To Call al-Bid With Cease-Fire Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2705160494 Abu Dhabi AL-ITTIHAD in Arabic 24 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2705160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Abu Dhabi AL-ITTIHAD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Reliable sources in Aden have told AL-ITTIHAD that 
the Yemeni president yesterday telephoned southern leader 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid and asked for an unconditional cease-fire. 
  Another source in the Socialist Party has also said that 
Mujahid Abu-Shawarib, the deputy prime minister in the Sanaa 
government, who is currently in Paris, the night before last 
telephoned some Socialist Party leaders in Aden asking them to 
approve a cease-fire and start immediate negotiations in Paris 
between Sanaa and Aden (three people from each party). The 
source said Aden does not object to a cease-fire and 
negotiations, on the condition that Sanaa withdraws all of its 
troops from the south. 

</TEXT>

