<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Iryani Threatens To End Dialogue if UNSC Intervenes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Iryani Threatens To End Dialogue if UNSC Intervenes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2705153894 London MBC Television in Arabic 1500 GMT 27 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2705153894 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Minister of Development and Planning 'Abd-al-Karim 
al-Iryani has threatened that Sanaa will close the door to 
dialogue with moderate and unionist leaders of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party if the UN Security Council [UNSC] intervenes in 
the Yemeni crisis. 
  He said Sanaa is awaiting a political message from Aden but 
did not disclose its contents. 
  Al-Iryani said one the reasons that military communiques 
have 
not been released since Tuesday is because the situation on the 
front is calm. 

</TEXT>

