<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Ahmar: UN Should `Rescue' Bosnia, Avoid Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Ahmar: UN Should `Rescue' Bosnia, Avoid Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2705174294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2705174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shaykh 'Abdallah Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar, the House of 
Representatives speaker, has stressed that what is happening in 
Yemen is an internal affair that is of no concern to the UN 
Security Council. He noted that if the UN Security Council is 
concerned about human rights, then it should rescue the people 
of Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  These statements emerged in a news conference held by the 
brother House of Representatives speaker in Abu Dhabi yesterday. 
He explained that the Yemeni people are offering everything for 
the sake of unity because it is dear and is worthy of 
sacrificing lives. 
  Shaykh 'Abdallah Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar said Yemeni unity is 
considered a foundation stone on the path of Arab unity. 
Therefore, he said, any recognition of the separatists is 
tantamount to hostility against the Yemeni people. 
  He added: Doors are open and bridges are built with all 
fraternal Arab and friendly states. The door to dialogue has 
not been closed with the unionists in the Socialist Party. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

