<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Ghani Leaves for UNSC Deliberations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Abd-al-Ghani Leaves for UNSC Deliberations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3005174994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3005174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] 'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani, Presidential Council 
member, has left Sanaa for Amman en route to New York. Before 
leaving Sanaa International Airport, he made the following 
statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA': 
  Entrusted by the Presidential Council and the Council of 
Ministers, I will represent the Republic of Yemen in the UN 
Security Council [UNSC] deliberations, which were requested by 
certain states. In this regard, we are interested in explaining 
the facts as they are to the UN Security Council to ensure that 
the results of these deliberations will be in harmony with the 
hopes of our people to preserve the country's unity and 
democratic march in the face of the conspiracy and malicious 
attack against unity and democracy by the secessionist elements 
in the Socialist Party leadership. These elements are trying to 
reverse history by insisting on returning to the pre-22 May 1990 
situation. 
  We will also brief the UN Security Council on the truth 
about 
what is happening in our country. It is an armed rebellion 
against constitutional legitimacy and a violation of the 
Constitution and a flagrant attack against citizens and their 
security and stability. The legitimate agencies' fulfillment of 
their tasks in the face of the armed rebellion reflect their 
national and constitutional responsibility to protect the 
sovereignty and stability of the homeland; it is also an 
internal affair and no one should interfere in it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

