<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister, UNDP Representative Discuss Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Prime Minister, UNDP Representative Discuss Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3005132494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3005132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar, the acting 
prime minister, today received brother 'Awni al-'Ani, resident 
representative of the UN Development Program [UNDP] in Sanaa. 
They discussed cooperation between our country and the UNDP and 
the urgent aid -- including food, clothes, medicine, medical 
equipment, and electricity generators -- which the UNDP is 
expected to provide to deal with the circumstances facing our 
country as a result of the crisis fabricated by the secessionist 
rebels in the Socialist Party leadership. 
  The UNDP resident representative expressed readiness to 
provide aid and help in the food and health fields and to 
revitalize the institutions that sustained damage. 

</TEXT>

