1700 GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2805180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister brother 'Abd-al-Wahhab 
al-Anisi received brother 'Ata Harun, the Egyptian ambassador in 
Sanaa today. They reviewed Yemeni developments and stressed that 
every effort must be made so Yemen's stability and security are 
spared. The meeting also addressed bilateral ties. Both noted 
the need to clear the air of Arab relations. 
  The deputy prime minister also received brother Mansur 
'Abdallah al-'Awadi, the Kuwaiti charge d'affaires in Sanaa. 
They discussed Yemeni developments. Both were in agreement as 
to the need to maintain Yemen's unity, security, and stability. 
They also underscored the brotherly relations that bind the 
Yemeni and Kuwaiti peoples. 

</TEXT>

