<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meeting To Support War Effort Nets 63 Million Riyals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meeting To Support War Effort Nets 63 Million Riyals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3005184894 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3005184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani, Presidential 
Council member and chairman of the Higher Committee for 
Receiving Donations, has attended a meeting at the Chamber of 
Industry and Commerce in Sanaa. The meeting was attended by 
members of the committee and a host of major businessmen and 
heads of public, mixed and private commercial and industrial 
institutions. The meeting was aimed at discussing the issue of 
supporting the war effort and organizing the process of 
receiving donations and public support for the effort to defend 
unity and constitutional legitimacy and to ease the damages 
resulting from the battles being waged by the forces defending 
constitutional legitimacy, unity, and democracy. 
  Speaking at the meeting, Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani 
explained that the battle being waged by the Armed Forces--the 
forces defending legitimacy and unity against the forces that 
are misled by the gang of apostasy and secession under war 
criminal 'Ali Salim al-Bid--is a battle that emphasizes 
adherence to Yemeni unity and rejection of partition. [passage 
omitted] 
  Addressing attendees, Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani said: 
This meeting is the first step toward public participation and 
beginning of supporting the war effort. He added: Today, you 
will set a good example for the people, who know how able you 
are. If they see that you have made substantial donations, they 
will undoubtedly follow your example and offer whatever they can. 
  Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani stressed that the committee 
is determined to reach every Yemeni in every governorate, 
district, subdistrict, and village to tell them: The door for 
donations is open. Donate whatever you can for the unity of 
your country. Al-Zandani indicated that the committee will 
control methods for disbursing collected donations. It will 
also work to spend donations appropriately. Civilian and 
military war casualties will be supported. Families of martyrs 
will be helped. Those who suffered losses will be compensated 
so as to stress the principle of joint liability. He indicated 
that there will be women's committees to collect donations from 
women. [passage omitted] 
  The Yemeni News Agency, SABA', has learned that the 
donations 
declared at the meeting amounted to 63.325 million riyals. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

