<F P=100> Nepal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pakistan's Bhutto Pays Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pakistan's Bhutto Pays Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives in Kathmandu </H4>

<F P=102> BK2405121194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1100 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2405121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, arrived 
today in Kathmandu on a three-day official visit to Nepal. She 
was received at the airport by the prime minister, Mr. Girija 
Prasad Koirala. Ms. Benazir Bhutto said she was delighted to be 
in Nepal. She said this is her first official visit to any SAARC 
[South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation] member 
country. It shows special importance that Pakistan attaches to 
developing its relations with Nepal. She said we will try to 
identify areas where we can cooperate so that we can consolidate 
our historic friendly relations with Nepal. 

</TEXT>

