<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hekmatyar's Attack Repulsed in Logar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hekmatyar's Attack Repulsed in Logar </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705183394 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Dari 1430 
GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Dari </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An attack of the Golboddin militia was aborted in 
Logar Province. Quoting a security source of the country, a 
BAKHTAR INFORMATION AGENCY correspondent reported: The infamous 
militia of Golboddin launched an attack against the positions of 
the Islamic Army at 0400 in Mandokhel in the center of Logar 
Province. The militias were forced to retreat as a result of 
the resistance of the mojahedin and soldiers of Brigade 800, 
Jehadi Division 36. The report says that two militia were 
killed and eight others were injured, and the enemy's one set of 
BM-1 rocket launchers was destroyed. 

</TEXT>

