<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khamene'i, Hashemi-Rafsanjani Mark 'Id al-Ghadir Khumm </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khamene'i, Hashemi-Rafsanjani Mark 'Id al-Ghadir Khumm </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2905135694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2905135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] [Announcer] In Tehran this 
morning, officials and authorities of the Islamic system 
gathered in Imam Khomeyni's mosque, may he be admitted to God's 
paradise, in order to offer congratulations on the occasion of 
the auspicious 'Id al-Ghadir Khumm, the 'id of guardianship 
[velayat] and imamate, to His Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i, the 
guardian of the cause of Muslims. 
  [Unidentified Correspondent] At this meeting, the honorable 
leader made a speech in which he offered his congratulations on 
the occasion of the great 'Id al-Ghadir to the Muslims and 
righteousness-seeking people of the world, and the faithful 
people of Iran. [passage omitted] 
  His Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i described the period of 
reconstruction and repair of the damages caused during the war 
as a sensitive and important stage in the history of the 
revolution. At the end of his speech, he said: 
  [Begin Khamene'i recording] Today is the stage of 
reconstruction. Today the people have the opportunity after a 
long war. For this very same sensitive reason, you can see that 
the world is attacking the productive policies of the Iranian 
people with poisoned arrows from all sides. It engages in 
propaganda, it engages in political games, it engages in 
security provocations, it engages in economic sabotage. The 
enemy does all it can, but thanks be to God, it is not 
successful in the majority of cases. In this era, the thing 
that can make you victorious, the thing that can build the 
nation, the thing that can keep the Iranian people on the 
political scene, the thing that can mobilize all forces in this 
holy path of construction is holding on to Islamic values with 
both hands. [crowd chants] [end recording] 
  [Announcer] Before the speech by the honorable leader, 
Hojjat 
ol-Eslam val Moslemin Hashemi-Rafsanjani, the president, 
delivered an address in which he offered his congratulations on 
the occasion of 'Id al-Ghadir to the honorable leader of the 
Islamic revolution. [passage omitted] Speaking about Imam 
'Ali's appointment, may peace be upon him, as the guardian of 
the Islamic ummah on 'Id al-Ghadir Khumm, the president said: 
The Muslim people of Iran rebelled through relying on the 
principle of guardianship and created the Islamic system. They 
have put the difficult phase of defense and the problems of the 
revolution behind them. Today, by using this very same divine 
blessing of guardianship, while neutralizing the carefully 
worked out plots of the revolution's enemies, it is successfully 
going through the difficult period of reconstruction and 
economic balance. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

