Daily Report 
<DATE1>  27 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Pushes UN Censure of Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Pushes UN Censure of Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Buwayz Expects U.S. Veto </H4>

<F P=102> NC2705173494 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 27 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2705173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz has announced that 
Foreign Ministry Secretary General Zafir al-Hasan will call the 
major powers' ambassadors in Lebanon tomorrow. He will discuss 
Lebanon's request for a Security Council meeting to debate the 
Lebanese complaint against Israel in the abduction of Lebanese 
citizen Mustafa al-Dirani. He said Lebanon expects the United 
States to use its veto power, but the Security Council must live 
up to its responsibilities. He expressed his belief that the 
United Nations could restore its credibility by taking 
appropriate action. [passage omitted] Answering journalists' 
questions, Foreign Minister Buwayz said: 
  [Begin Buwayz recording] Of course the wavering in dealing 
with Israel by the Security Council, the United Nations, and 
several influential and major powers is no longer a secret. We 
are at a stage where numerous Israeli aggressions are 
overlooked. Hence, we believe that the United Nations should 
regain its credibility by taking an appropriate decision on this 
issue. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-35320 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes104_j_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-104 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's al-'Attas Visits as Envoy for Vice President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemen's al-'Attas Visits as Envoy for Vice President </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives From Abu Dhabi </H4>

<F P=102> LD2905131794 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1159 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2905131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kuwait, 29 May (KUNA) -- Haydar Abu-Bakr 
al-'Attas, envoy of the secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party, arrived here today from Abu Dhabi on a two-day 
visit to Kuwait during which he will give a message to the amir 
of Kuwait. [passage omitted] 
  In an arrival statement to KUNA, the Yemeni envoy said he is 
confident that his meetings with the amir of Kuwait and Kuwaiti 
officials will be successful. He stated that they will discuss 
the situation in Yemen "as a result of the war launched by the 
military command in Sanaa in the same spirit and with the same 
rationale as that with which the perfidious war was launched 
against Kuwait." 
  Al-'Attas praised the efforts made by Arab states to halt 
the 
war and said that these efforts are appreciated by the Yemeni 
people. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

