<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Issues Decree on Amnesty for `Misled Ones' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bid Issues Decree on Amnesty for `Misled Ones' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2905192994 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1650 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2905192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1650 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, chairman of the 
Presidential Council, today issued Republican Decree No. 5 for 
1994 concerning a general amnesty for the misled ones 
[al-mugharrari bihim]. The first article of the decree provides 
for a general amnesty for all those who have been misled, and 
who have participated, directly or indirectly, in exploding the 
situation militarily, and in committing aggression against the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen. It also amnesties the sons of the 
areas against which aggression has been committed, who were 
forced by circumstances or concern about their own safety and 
lives to work against the sons of their own areas, their tribes, 
and their state. 
  The second article of the decree provides for the 
regularization of the status of those mentioned in the 
above-mentioned first article, if they join in the defense of 
the Democratic Republic of Yemen, in emulation of their 
colleagues. 
  The third article of the decree states that the decree takes 
effect from the date of its issuance, and that it shall be 
published in the official gazette. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

