<H3> <TI>   `Source' Denies Aden Proposed Unconditional Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source' Denies Aden Proposed Unconditional Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2905120694 Kuwait Radio Kuwait in Arabic 1000 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2905120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait Radio Kuwait </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden radio broadcast a statement this morning by a 
responsible source in the Democratic Republic of Yemen -- which 
has been declared in the south -- denying Sanaa's assertion 
that officials in the Yemeni Socialist Party have proposed an 
unconditional cease-fire in Yemen. 
  The source declared that Aden insists on two basic 
conditions 
for a cease-fire. These are the withdrawal of all northern 
forces to positions behind the previous borders between the two 
parts of Yemen, and the holding of direct talks with the Aden 
government. 

</TEXT>

