<H3> <TI>   Former Southern President Voices Support for Unity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former Southern President Voices Support for Unity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3005055694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3005055694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Brother 'Ali Nasir Muhammad, former secretary 
general of the [Yemeni] Socialist Party [and former South Yemeni 
President] addressed a cable to the brother Presidential Council 
chairman. Following is the text: 
  Your Excellency Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih, Presidential Council chairman, may God keep you. 
[passage omitted] 
  We strongly believe that there is still motivation for 
unity, 
that there will be no future without unity, and that defeat is 
awaiting all those who antagonize it, represented in the 
tendencies that are opposed to unity and democracy. 
  We are fully confident that the unified state is the only 
way 
to confront every crisis and failure in any field. It is also 
the sole way to deal with both large and small mistakes. It can 
contain all negative results of this war and fighting between 
brothers. The values of unity, democracy, and life will triumph 
forever. 
  Unity is the cause of life and destiny for our people in 
Yemen. It is the cause of generations and the future, and it is 
not linked to individuals, therefore, we are confident that our 
people will not allow the reversal of unity and the return to 
the stage before 22 May 1990. [Word indistinct] their strong 
and unwavering faith in unity as a source of strength and 
dignity that concerns their future and development. 
  Finally, we assure you and our people of our principled and 
firm support for Yemeni unity, democracy, and the ambitions of 
our Yemeni people to realize their happy unionist society. 
  We wish your excellency continued good health and happiness, 
and accept our sincerest greetings. 
  [Signed] Your brother President 'Ali Nasir Muhammad 

</TEXT>

