BFN 

  [Text] The Yemeni Unionist Alliance Party has stated that 
the house of brother Muhammad Abduh Nu'man, the founder of the 
party, has been stormed and searched in Sanaa. Some of his 
possessions were looted. The statement said this must be 
considered as the beginning of a unique type of terrorism, 
oppression, and arbitrariness. 
  In an official statement issued by its secretariat general, 
and distributed in Aden yesterday, the Yemeni Unionist Alliance 
