<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces Deny Missile Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armed Forces Deny Missile Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2905114194 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1114 GMT 
29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2905114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A military source in Sanaa categorically denied that 
government troops had fired any missiles on Aden yesterday or 
today. The source stressed that only the city's airport was 
targeted by Yemeni Armed Forces artillery. 
  In a statement transmitted today by the official Yemeni News 
Agency, SABA', the source said that the objective of the 
shelling is to prevent the secessionists from using the airport 
to launch raids with warplanes on defenseless citizens and the 
forces of unity and legitimacy. 
  The source stressed that none of the civilian installations 
or residential areas in Aden will ever be a target of the 
artillery shelling. The source explained, however, that all 
military targets in the city are now within the range of the 
unity forces' artillery, which is now engaging them from a 
distance of no more 14 km. 

</TEXT>

