<H3> <TI>   Sporadic Fighting Reported on al-'Anad Front </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sporadic Fighting Reported on al-'Anad Front </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3105072594 Paris AFP in English 0603 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3105072594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Yemen, May 31 (AFP)--Northern and Southern 
Yemeni troops on Tuesday exchanged sporadic artillery fire 
around this southern city, an AFP correspondent reported. 
  The fighting was mainly at the al-'Anad front, 60 kilometers 
(36 miles) north of Aden and Abyan 35 kilometers (21 miles) east 
of the city. 
  Several MiG-21 were spotted taking off from Aden Airport. 
  The fighting continued as the UN Security Council was due 
later in the day to discuss the civil war that erupted on May 5 
between northern forces of President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and 
those of his southern rival 'Ali Salim al-Bid. 
  Al-Bid proclaimed a breakaway Yemen Democratic Republic on 
May 20, but it has not been recognised internationally. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

