<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Draws Islamic Figure Into Authority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Draws Islamic Figure Into Authority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105133594 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 31 May 94 p 17 </F>
<F P=103> JN3105133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Riyad Mansur in Amman] </F>
  [Excerpt] Yasir 'Arafat, chairman of the Palestinian 
self-rule authority has apparently succeeded in drawing a 
prominent West Bank Muslim Brotherhood leader into participating 
in the Palestinian Authority, conflicting with the position of 
the Hamas Movement, which was set up in 1987 from the 
Palestinian organization of the Muslim Brotherhood. 
  Hamas did not deny that this Islamic personality is 
currently 
in Tunis, but emphasized that Sa'id Bilal was fired from the 
Muslim Brotherhood and has no links with Hamas. Hamas said 
Bilal's invitation to Tunis was made within the framework of 
'Arafat's preparations to detonate a media bomb by announcing 
the participation of this person in the Palestinian authority. 
  Hamas recalled how 'Arafat had given Palestine National 
Council [PNC] membership to five Islamic personalities, and then 
reports said that they were Hamas representatives in the PNC. 
Hamas added 'Arafat wants to repeat the same tactic now and 
allege that Hamas is with the Palestinian Authority. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

