<H3> <TI>   Gaza Security Chief Requests Surrender of Murderers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gaza Security Chief Requests Surrender of Murderers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3105205994 Jerusalem AL-NAHAR in Arabic 29 May 94 p 1, 7 </F>
<F P=103> NC3105205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-NAHAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Gaza -- Major General Nasr Yusuf, commander of 
the Palestinian national security forces in the Gaza Strip, has 
affirmed that no agreement has yet been reached with Hamas, 
because we insist on the surrender of those who murdered two 
citizens the day before yesterday. We have informed the party 
to which they belong about this. 
  He emphasized again that the security forces will pursue 
anyone who kidnaps or harasses any citizen or who tampers with 
the security of the citizens. There is only one Authority in 
the Gaza Strip, and this Authority has been entrusted with 
safeguarding the security of the citizens and punishing those 
who violate the law. 
  Asked whether an ultimatum has been given to these parties, 
he explained that the responsible party has been officially 
requested to hand over those who carried out the killing, and we 
will pursue the murderers. It would be important to us and to 
them if they hand over the murderers, he said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

