<H3> <TI>   Gaza Security Forces Detain Islamic Jihad Activist </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gaza Security Forces Detain Islamic Jihad Activist </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2705145594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 27 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2705145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinian security forces in the Gaza Strip 
have detained an Islamic Jihad activist. According to Islamic 
leaders in Gaza the detainee, Hani al-'Abd, is a journalist 
working in a local communications center which is connected with 
Islamic Jihad. Islamic Jihad people in Gaza say that Palestinian 
policemen searched for al-'Abd several days ago. Since he was 
not at home, he came voluntarily to the police headquarters in 
Gaza, where he was detained. Palestinian security elements in 
Gaza confirm that the man was detained. They refused to say 
why, but noted that he is the only person currently jailed in 
the Gaza prison. 

</TEXT>

