<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commander on Hamas Decision To Stop Killing Agents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commander on Hamas Decision To Stop Killing Agents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3105211094 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 31 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC3105211094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Zaki Abu-Halawah and Muhammad Abu-Khudayr] </F>
  [Excerpts] Jericho -- Brigadier General al-Hajj Isma'il 
Jabr, commander of the Palestinian national security forces in 
Jericho, has welcomed the decision of the Islamic Resistance 
Movement, Hamas, to stop liquidating collaborators. He said: 
We view this decision with great appreciation. This decision 
will strengthen our national unity and mutual understanding to 
overcome the current problems and frustrate all those who are 
wagering on intra-Palestinian conflict. 
  In an exclusive interview with AL-QUDS, Jabr said that this 
decision will restore to the Palestinian Authority its prestige, 
power, and respect. This is a positive decision that will 
ensure the success of the political process. 
  He affirmed that the Palestinian forces will resort to law 
to 
bring to account any Palestinian who violates security, order, 
or the law. Anarchy will not be tolerated. 
  Jabr expressed surprise at Israeli statements calling for 
moving Palestinian institutions from Jerusalem to the 
Palestinian self-rule areas. He said that such statements 
contradict the provisions of the Palestinian-Israeli agreement, 
which put off the discussion of the future of Jerusalem to the 
final stage. These statements are unilateral and unacceptable 
to the Palestinians. 
  He said that preparations and construction are underway to 
complete the main passage way for the residents of Gaza and 
Jericho. The dignity of the Palestinians will be respected on 
this passage way. [passage omitted] 
  Regarding the preparations for the arrival of Palestinian 
president Yasir 'Arafat in Jericho, Jabr said that preparations 
are going ahead. We are awaiting instructions on the arrival 
date. There are special security arrangements that cannot be 
divulged now, he said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

