<H3> <TI>   Al-Rujub Movements Restricted Due to Pronouncements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Rujub Movements Restricted Due to Pronouncements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3105133594 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1300 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA3105133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin revealed today that 
the movements of Jibril al-Rujub, head of the PLO's security 
apparatus in Jericho, have been restricted and that he has been 
barred from leaving the city in the wake of his recent 
pronouncements. 
  During a visit to the Bedouin town of Lagiya in the Negev 
last Friday, al-Rujub stated that the autonomy was the first 
phase on the road to the establishment of a Palestinian state 
with Jerusalem as its capital, and that the Palestinians would 
not cease their struggle until Jerusalem has been liberated. 
Al-Rujub also called for the continuation of the armed struggle 
from within the boundaries of the autonomy. 

</TEXT>

