<H3> <TI>   Hamas To Establish Political Party in Territories </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas To Establish Political Party in Territories </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105171594 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1200 GMT 31 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3105171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Amman, Ibrahim Ghawshah, official spokesman for 
the Hamas Movement, has stated that the Movement intends to 
establish a political party in the occupied territories that 
comprises all the opposition forces in the territories. 
  Ghawshah explained that the party will deal with political 
tasks that would be agreed upon and that will be in line with 
the changes and current facts on the ground in the Palestinian 
arena, particularly following the implementation of autonomy in 
Gaza and Jericho. Ghawshah added that this issue is being 
discussed within Hamas, which holds consultations with its 
allies within the Alliance of Palestinian Forces, or the 10 
Palestinian opposition factions which have their headquarters in 
Damascus. 

</TEXT>

