<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Reportedly Refuses To Surrender Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Reportedly Refuses To Surrender Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3105210594 Jerusalem AL-NAHAR in Arabic 29 May 94 p 3, 7 </F>
<F P=103> NC3105210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-NAHAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gaza -- One of the leaders of the Islamic 
Resistance Movement, Hamas, has affirmed that Hamas welcomes the 
Palestinian Authority but will not participate in it. The 
statement was made during a visit by Major General Nasr Yusuf, 
commander of the Palestinian security forces in the Gaza Strip, 
to a number of Islamic centers in the area and his meeting with 
a number of Hamas officials. During this visit, Maj. Gen. Yusuf 
expressed his readiness to cooperate on several issues with the 
Palestinian Authority. 
  In this regard, Shaykh Ahmad Bahr, head of the Islamic 
Society, clarified the Islamic Movement's position under the 
Palestinian Authority, and dealt with the issue of the 
collection of weapons from the members of the 'Izz-al-Din 
al-Qassam Battalions. He said: Neither Hamas nor its military 
wing will agree to surrender any of the weapons they collected 
over a period of many years as long as arms-carrying settlers 
remain inside the Gaza Strip. He also explained that the 
self-rule agreement does not compel Hamas to respond to 
everything contained in it, because Hamas does not accept 
self-rule. 
  Referring to the issue of enlistment in the Palestinian 
police force, Shaykh Bahr said Hamas has not directed its 
members to enlist in the Palestinian police. 

</TEXT>

