<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   EC Proposes Absorbing 100,000 Refugees From Lebanon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EC Proposes Absorbing 100,000 Refugees From Lebanon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2705162094 Dubayy AL-BAYAN in Arabic 25 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2705162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Dubayy AL-BAYAN </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman -- AL-BAYAN has learned that the EC has 
adopted a plan to solve the Palestinian refugees problem in 
Lebanon, and that the EC member states have proposed this plan 
at the refugees committee meetings within the framework of the 
multilateral talks. 
  Palestinian sources in Amman told AL-BAYAN that the Italian 
ambassador to Lebanon has briefed the leaders of the opposition 
factions on this plan, which includes the absorption of 
approximately 100,000 Palestinians academicians in the EC 
states, and granting them the nationalities of these states. 
The plan also includes settling the reamining refugees in 
Lebanon and granting them Lebanese nationality, but without 
granting them the right to participate in elections, in order to 
avoid the disruption of the sectarian balance in Lebanon. 
  These sources added that the actual implementation of the 
plan has begun, and that the Lebanese Government has begun to 
grant citizenships to a number of refugees. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-35378 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes105dd_94022" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-105 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  27 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Release of 'Arafat's Wife's Uncle Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Release of 'Arafat's Wife's Uncle Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2705153094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 27 May 94 pp 
1, 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM2705153094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Reports by 'Ali Salih in London and AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
bureau in Tunis: "'Arafat Releases His Wife's Uncle"] 
  [Excerpt] Palestinian sources within the PLO have 
confirmed that the night before last 'Arafat released George 
Hawwa, the uncle of his wife Suha whom he had ordered arrested 
five days ago for interrogation in connection with a corruption 
case. 
  The sources said that George Hawwa, the businessman who 
lives 
in London, was accused of complicity in a bribery case involving 
foreign companies he tried to conclude contracts with in the 
name of the PLO. Other sources in Tunis say that he had sent 
messages to the trade attaches at foreign embassies in Tunis 
informing them of the formation of an investment company called 
"Parly" [as transliterated] and that he was ready to make deals 
with them for projects in areas in the autonomy region and in 
the occupied territory. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

