<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministers of Non-Aligned Movement Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministers of Non-Aligned Movement Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Velayati Denies Request To Host Next Summit </H4>

<F P=102> NC0106095294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0812 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (MENA) -- MENA has learned that the 
issue of choosing a host country for the Nonaligned Movement's 
next summit has not been decided yet, despite some rumors that 
Iran, Morocco, and Egypt may submit requests. 
  In a statement to MENA, Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar 
Velayati denied that Iran will submit a request if any of the 
Latin American group countries does not ask to host the summit, 
according to the geographical order under which the movement 
operates. 
  Egyptian diplomatic sources said that if there is no 
candidate from the Latin American countries, one of the Asian 
group countries may be nominated to host the next summit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

