<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Junblatt Welcomes Planned Army Deployment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Junblatt Welcomes Planned Army Deployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3105105694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 31 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3105105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Progressive Socialist Party [PSP] sources have 
stated that Minister Walid Junblatt has received a new plan from 
the Army Command on a broader military deployment as a prelude 
to the return of the evacuees. This plan will be implemented in 
the mountain area between 9 and 15 June. The Army is estimated 
at 5,000 to 7,000 Lebanese troops and will be deployed in most 
of the mountain villages and towns, particularly the villages 
that the evacuees will return to during the summer. The force 
will erect fixed and mobile roadblocks at the entrances of the 
villages, which were the scenes of various problems during the 
war, to ensure the security of the citizens. 
  The PSP sources added that Minister Junblatt has welcomed 
the 
details of the plan and that he briefed the PSP leadership on 
the deployment process. The sources noted that Minister 
Junblatt has praised the role of the Army and of General Lahhud 
before the popular delegations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

