<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Bahrain </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets With Amir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With Amir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105133494 Manama WAKH in Arabic 0950 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3105133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Manama, 31 May (WAKH) -- His Highness Shaykh 'Isa 
Bin-Salman Al Khalifah, received here today Haydar Abu-Bakr 
al-'Attas, envoy of 'Ali Salim al-Bid, secretary general of the 
Yemeni Socialist Party, who conveyed a message to his highness 
from al-Bid dealing with latest developments in Yemen. 
  Al-'Attas briefed his highness the amir of Bahrain on the 
latest developments in Yemen and the efforts aimed to stop 
fighting between brothers in Yemen. 
  Shaykh 'Isa regretted [words indistinct] fighting between 
brothers in Yemen and said he hoped this bloody fighting would 
stop and that differences would be resolved through 
negotiations. His highness said the regrettable and bloody 
events in Yemen will have repercussions on the Arab and Islamic 
[words indistinct]. 
  The amir of Bahrain called on both sides in Yemen to resort 
to reason and logic in order to preserve Yemen and its brotherly 
people, and expressed hope that the Arab [word indistinct] 
efforts would succeed in halting fighting in Yemen and restoring 
peace, security, and stability to this sisterly country. 
  The meeting was attended by Shaykh Muhammad Bin-Khalifah Al 
Khalifah, interior minister; Shaykh Khalid Bin-'Abdallah Al 
Khalifah, housing minister; Yusuf Irhamah al-Dawsari, head of 
the Amiri Court; and Nabil Ibrahim Qambar, director general of 
the Foreign Ministry's Protocol Department. 

</TEXT>

