  [Text] A responsible source from the command of the Armed 
Forces of the Democratic Repubic of Yemen [DRY] commented on the 
statements made by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and broadcast by Sanaa 
radio, which were given out to foreign media, which reported 
that his forces were currently advancing on Hadramawt to mop up 
what he described as the last pockets of the gang of apostasy 
and secession. 
  The source commented: We are disgusted to hear in these 
statements what does not fatten or satisfy hunger [Koranic 
verse]. We inform the public that the war being fought in our 
country today enters its second month, and that the forces of 
the DRY are steadfast, delivering successive blows against the 
forces of 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih on all fronts. 
  The source said battles are currently being fought in 
Shabwah 
Governorate, hundreds of kilometres away from the Governorate of 
Hadramawt, which 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih only dreams of reaching. 
This he can do only if his forces can burrow underground until 
they get to Hadramawt. The source stressed that the masses of 
the Shabwah Governorate and our Armed Forces are supported by 
the masses of the Ma'rib Governorate, and that between them they 
are delivering successive blows against the forces of 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and are forcing them into retreat and surrender. 

</TEXT>

