<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Accuses Saudi Arabia, Gulf States of Interference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa Accuses Saudi Arabia, Gulf States of Interference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0106105094 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1005 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0106105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] New York, 1 Jun (INA) -- Yemen has officially 
accused the Gulf states, led by Saudi Arabia, of interfering in 
the internal affairs of the Republic of Yemen. 
  This is contained in an official message addressed to the 
Security Council by Yemeni UN Ambassador 'Abdallah al-Ashtal. 
  In the message, Yemen said it considers the call for 
convening a Security Council meeting to be interference in its 
internal affairs, which conflicts with Paragraph 7 of Article 2 
of the UN Charter that says nothing in the charter justifies UN 
interference in affairs that are purely part of the sovereignty 
of any country, and that nothing in the charter stipulates that 
member states can call for a discussion of such issues. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

