<H3> <TI>   More on Premier's Meeting With Palestinians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Premier's Meeting With Palestinians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105195694 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 1900 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3105195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News at Ten"] </F>
  [Text] Four members of the new Palestinian National 
Authority [PNA], which will administer Gaza and Jericho, met 
Prime Minister 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali. 
  The Palestinian delegation included Ilyas Frayj, Zakariya 
al-Agha, 'Azmi al-Shu'aybi, and 'Abd-al-Hafiz al-Ashhab. 
  Prime Minister al-Majali reaffirmed Jordan's support to the 
new authority which will govern Palestinian self-rule areas, and 
said Jordan's coordination with the new authority is an absolute 
necessity. 
  Mr. Frayj said their talks with the prime minister also 
touched on the makeup of the new authority: 
  [Begin recording] [Frayj in progress]...with full openness 
with the prime minister, and we have one strategic aim is to 
achieve full cooperation and coordination with our Jordanian 
brothers. 
  [Correspondent Maha al-Sha'ir] Have you discussed specifics 
with respect to the coordination between both governments? 
  [Frayj] We come here to Jordan to discuss, each one of us, 
how to do the best coordination with the ministries he is in 
charge of. 
  [Al-Sha'ir] When do you expect the signing of the economic 
agreement between the PLO and Jordan? 
  [Al-Agha] I expect it will be within the next few days. 
There will be a visit by Palestinian officials, including 
Chairman 'Arafat, to Jordan, and all these issues will be 
discussed and concluded during this visit. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

