<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Ready To Brief House on Peace Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Ready To Brief House on Peace Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0106115894 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1100 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0106115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali has said 
that the government is ready to acquaint parliament members with 
the latest political developments in the region, especially 
those related to the peace process. 
  The prime minister was responding to a proposal by a 
parliament member who called for a special meeting between 
members of the lower house of parliament and the government. 
  Dr. al-Majali said the parliament has not previously asked 
the government for such a meeting, adding that the government is 
always ready to meet parliamentarians' demands. 
  The speaker of the lower house Mr. Tahir al-Masri said the 
meeting will be scheduled for next week. Mr. al-Masri was 
speaking this morning during a session of the house in the 
presence of the prime minister and cabinet ministers. 

</TEXT>

