<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hasan: Arabs `Cautiously Optimistic' on Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hasan: Arabs `Cautiously Optimistic' on Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0106114394 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1100 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0106114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Royal Highness Crown Prince has said that Arabs 
were cautiously optimistic about peace with Israel. 
  This came in a speech before an annual meeting of the UN 
agency caring for Palestinian refugees, read on behalf of his 
royal highness by Minister of State Mr. 'Adil 'Irshayd. 
  The crown prince said the continued frustrations Arab people 
have lived over the past two years are regressing now, and are 
being replaced by cautious optimism that the peace process will 
continue its march until it reaches a comprehensive solution. 
  But Prince Hasan added that the feelings of fear and anxiety 
are still there, referring to unresolved Arab-Israeli issues and 
agreements signed but never implemented. 
  Prince Hasan said the UN Relief and Works Agency should 
continue health and education services until the plight of 3 
million refugees were settled in a fair and permanent way that 
secures their rights in line with UN resolutions. 

</TEXT>

