<H3> <TI>   Lebanese Foreign Minister Arrives for Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lebanese Foreign Minister Arrives for Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Makes Statement </H4>

<F P=102> JN3005061194 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 0400 GMT 
30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3005061194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lebanese Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz arrived in 
Amman yesterday evening to take part in the 17th ministerial 
session of the ESCWA [Economic and Social Commission for Western 
Asia], which opened its meetings in Amman yesterday. 
  Upon arrival, the Lebanese minister expressed happiness over 
his visit to the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan. He said the 
Lebanese people cherish and appreciate the Jordanian people and 
that His Majesty King Husayn occupies a special place in the 
hearts of all the Lebanese. 
  He added that during his visit he will take part in the 
ESCWA's ministerial session, especially since Lebanon is one of 
the countries nominated to serve as the headquarters for this 
commission. 
  On the peace process, the Lebanese minister said that after 
more than three years since the launching of the peace process 
and the Madrid conference, this process has not achieved the 
hopes that had been pinned on it. He asserted that the two 
cosponsors of the Madrid conference should continue to play an 
active role in line with the requirements of the Madrid process 
through the resolutions of international legitimacy and to play 
the role of a fair broker. 
  The Lebanese minister noted that he will meet with several 
Jordanian officials to discuss Arab developments of interest to 
both countries. 

</TEXT>

