<H3> <TI>   Musa, Iran's Velayati Do Not `Rule Out' Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa, Iran's Velayati Do Not `Rule Out' Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0106094394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0900 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (MENA) -- Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
has emphasized that nothing is impeding a meeting with his 
Iranian counterpart, 'Ali Akbar Velayati, who is taking part in 
the Nonaligned Movement Conference being held in Cairo. 
  In a statement to MENA, Velayati said that he does not rule 
out a meeting with 'Amr Musa. Velayati refused to either deny 
or confirm the reports that a meeting will be held with 'Amr 
Musa today. The Iranian foreign minister declined to comment 
whether the talks will deal with relations between Egypt and 
Iran. 
  Diplomatic Egyptian sources said that Egypt is ready to hold 
any meeting with the heads of delegations participating in the 
conference. 

