<F P=103> NC3105134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The People's Assembly Arab Affairs Committee 
expressed its deep regret for the unacceptable provocative 
measures that the Sudanese Government has recently adopted 
against Egyptian property and nationals in Sudan. 
  In a statement it has issued, the committee noted that these 
measures are just part of the unacceptable actions that have 
become a characteristic of the ruling Sudanese regime because of 
the internal and external crises gripping it. 
  The committee affirmed that Egypt cannot be provoked and 
deeply cares for the interests of the Sudanese people and the 
close relations between the two peoples, which no irresponsible 
behavior can harm. 

