<H3> <TI>   National Dialogue Committee Holds First Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Dialogue Committee Holds First Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0106091994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0804 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (MENA) -- The committee in charge of 
preparation for the national dialogue held its first meeting at 
the People's Assembly headquarters today under the chairmanship 
of Dr. Mustafa Khalil, deputy leader of the National Democratic 
Party [NDP] and the committee moderator. 
  The meeting was attended by Dr. Yusuf Wali, deputy prime 
minister and NDP secretary general; Minister of Information 
Safwat al-Sharif; Kamal al-Shadhili, minister of state for the 
People's Assembly and Consultative Council affairs; party and 
trade union leaders; and a number of university professors and 
public figures. 
  The committee will discuss the organization of the national 
dialogue conference and its agenda, as well as determining the 
national forces who will participate in it. 
  Upon the completion of its task, the committee will submit a 
report to President Husni Mubarak on the issues to be agreed 
upon before calling the general conference to session. 
  MENA has learned that the parties participating in the 
dialogue have compiled working papers explaining their views on 
the issues they will raise during the national dialogue. 

</TEXT>

