<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shin Bet Kills Hamas Fugitives North of Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shin Bet Kills Hamas Fugitives North of Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3105163794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 31 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3105163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] fugitives 
were killed this afternoon in the village of al-Ram, north of 
Jerusalem, during an operation by the Shin Bet and the Israel 
Police special antiterror unit. 
  Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that one of the two men 
killed was Yusuf Naji, the murderer of the late Shin Bet agent 
No'am Kohen. As may be recalled, Naji was a former collaborator 
with the authorities and Kohen was his handler. 
  In the course of a meeting, Naji and his accomplices shot 
No'am Kohen and his two bodyguards. No'am Kohen died as a 
result of the shooting and the Shin Bet has been conducting a 
manhunt after Naji ever since. 

</TEXT>

