<H3> <TI>   Commissioner Addresses Knesset on Water Quality </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commissioner Addresses Knesset on Water Quality </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0106105394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 1 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0106105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Water Commissioner Gid'on Tzur says that autonomy 
agreements could critically endanger Israel's water supply. In 
a briefing to the Knesset State Audit Committee, the 
commissioner said the country's water supply could be damaged by 
seeping sewage and industrial waste from the autonomous regions. 
He said he believes that Israel should have secured better 
guarantees for its water rights during negotiations. 

</TEXT>

