<H3> <TI>   Spy Plane `Violations' Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spy Plane `Violations' Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2805093994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0816 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2805093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New York, 28 May (INA)--Iraq has protested the 
continued violations of Iraqi airspace by a U.S. U-2 spy plane 
on the pretext of conducting air surveys for the Special 
Commission. 
  In a message to UN Secretary General Dr. Butrus-Ghali from 
Foreign Minister Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf, Iraq stressed that 
this plane, having flown from its base in Saudi Arabia, violated 
Iraqi airspace on 25 April and 11 and 24 May. After overflying 
vast areas of the country, it flew back to Saudi territory. 
  The message restates that this plane is used for purposes 
other than those specified by the UN Security Council and that 
its activity harms Iraq's sovereignty and security. 

</TEXT>

