<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] A delegation from the Patriotic Union of 
Kurdistan [PUK] and a delegation from the Kurdistan Democratic 
Party [KDP] held a meeting Monday [30 May] evening at the PUK 
Political Bureau headquarters in Irbil. Ahmad al-Jalabi, 
president of the Executive Council of the Unified Iraqi National 
Congress, attended the meeting. [passage omitted] 
  At the meeting, which was characterized by a cordial and 
brotherly atmosphere and a high sense of responsibility, the 
current situation in Kurdistan in general and the security 
situation in Irbil in particular were discussed. At their 
one-hour meeting the conferees stressed the need to maintain 
calm and security. 

