<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Barzani Denies Asking Iran To Mediate in Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Barzani Denies Asking Iran To Mediate in Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105184194 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 31 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3105184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Huda al-Husayni from London] </F>
  [Text] Mas'ud Barzani, leader of the Democratic Party of 
Kurdistan [DPK], has told Radio Monte Carlo that the fighting 
between his party and the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan [PUK] 
under Jalal Talabani is the result of the differences in 
viewpoints on how to tackle matters, particularly how to run 
Iraqi Kurdistan and settle political issues. 
  Barzani said that Talabani's forces occupied the Parliament 
building on 3 May as coupists usually do as the first step. 
Barzani denied reports that the Iranian Revolutionary Guard are 
fighting on the side of his forces. He also denied that he has 
asked for Iran's mediation. He said that it was Talabani who 
asked Tehran to host a meeting of the leaders of the warring 
Iraqi Kurdish parties. 
  Mas'ud Barzani also stressed that no one in Iraqi Kurdistan 
has prevented Talabani, who is in Damascus, from returning to 
his headquarters, and that on his request the allied forces 
military coordination office placed a helicopter at his disposal 
to bring him to Kurdistan. However, Talabani changed his mind. 
  Barzani accused the PUK forces of killing all civilian and 
military prisoners who belong to the DPK. 
  In his interview with Radio Monte Carlo, Mas'ud Barzani 
admitted that the fighting has weakened the democratic process 
in Kurdistan and has not enhanced the status of Iraqi Kurds in 
the eyes of the western countries. On the contrary, the 
fighting has embarrassed some of these countries. He emphasized 
the need to stop the fighting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

