<H3> <TI>   Al-Sahhaf Confers With Counterparts in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Sahhaf Confers With Counterparts in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Holds Talks With SRV Minister </H4>

<F P=102> JN3105140194 Baghdad INA in Arabic 2050 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3105140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 May (INA) -- Foreign Minister Muhammad 
Sa'id al-Sahhaf, the head of Iraq's delegation to the 
Non-Aligned conference met with Norodom Sira, the foreign 
minister of Vietnam [name and title as received] here today. 
  Mr. al-Sahhaf indicated to the Vietnamese minister a shift 
favoring Iraq in the UN Security Council. He also noted that 
more permanent and nonpermanent members of the council, as well 
as the international community, are demanding an end to the 
sanctions. Al-Sahhaf further noted that Iraq was complying with 
the obligations stipulated in Security Council resolutions. 
  Al-Sahhaf impressed on the Vietnamese minister the need for 
the Council to honor its obligations to Iraq. He hoped that 
when the council next reviews Iraq's compliance with the 
Security Council resolutions, it will take a fair and clear-cut 
stand leading to the lifting of the sanctions. The two 
ministers also talked about relations between Iraq and Vietnam. 
  The IRAQI NEWS AGENCY correspondent in Cairo reports that 
the 
Vietnamese minister renewed his country's support for removing 
the sanctions as a matter of urgency. The Vietnamese Government 
and people, he said, view Iraq's performance under more than 
three years of the sanctions with pride and admiration. 
  The two ministers also reviewed the agenda of the 
Non-Aligned 
conference, which opens tomorrow, both agreeing on the need for 
the movement to be strengthened and its principles upheld. 
  Iraq's permanent Arab League delegate attended the session. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

