BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (INA) -- Foreign Minister Muhammad 
Sa'id al-Sahhaf, head of the Iraqi delegation to the meetings of 
the Nonaligned Movement [NAM], met here today with Yemeni 
Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah. 
  Basindwah explained to al-Sahhaf the plots being hatched 
against Yemen's unity with the aim of undermining the people's 
achievements. 
  The Yemeni minister stressed his country's rejection of any 
interference in its domestic affairs by any party because what 
is happening in Yemen is an internal affair and because the 
legitimate authority and the people are determined to preserve 
unity and to side with the constitutional government to foil the 
objectives of the separatists. 
  For his part, Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf reiterated Iraq's 
firm 
position in support of the legitimate government in fraternal 
Yemen and preserving its unity. 
  During the meeting, they also discussed the current Arab 
situation, ways of enhancing joint Arab action, and the items on 
the agenda of the nonaligned meeting in Cairo. 
  The meeting was attended by Dr. Nabil Najm, Iraq's permanent 
envoy to the Arab League. 

