<H3> <TI>   Saddam Orders Examination Monitors' Fees Raised </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Orders Examination Monitors' Fees Raised </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105135294 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3105135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chairing the first session of the cabinet, His 
Excellency President Saddam Husayn has ordered that the fees of 
monitors at general examination centers be raised to 50 dinars 
per day. This was disclosed by Minister of Education Hikmat 
'Abdallah al-Bazzaz to the Iraqi News Agency. This generous act 
on the part of his excellency the leader president, al-Bazzaz 
said, is another addition to his numerous such favors in support 
of a superior educational process. The move doubles the 
educationists' responsibility to carry out their monitoring 
duties in the test centers so as to raise a generation armed 
with science and faith. 
  In the name of the teaching profession, the minister 
promised His Excellency leader, mujahid President Saddam Husayn 
that efforts will be maximized to enhance the scientific and 
educational standard and quicken the pace of the march of 
advancement Iraq is experiencing in all domains. 

</TEXT>

