<H3> <TI>   Daily Suggests Reconsidering Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Suggests Reconsidering Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106083294 Tehran IRNA in English 0746 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 1, IRNA -- A morning daily here 
Wednesday [1 June] recommended the Iranian authorities to 
reconsider Tehran's relations with London and take a more 
calculated and deliberate stance vis-a-vis Britain. 
  Criticizing the recent British charges against Iran 
including 
the alleged Tehran's support for the Irish Republican Army (IRA) 
and the expelling of Iranian charge d'affaires from Britain, 
`JOMHURI-E ESLAMI' wrote in a commentary that the British 
officials have launched an "extensive propaganda campaign 
against the Islamic Repulic of Iran with an aim to satisfy 
American statesmen." 
  The article referred to the forthcoming visit to Britain of 
the U.S. President Bill Clinton, scheduled next Sunday, and said 
that the British mass media, by resorting to fabricated 
allegations, once again are trying to accuse Iran of having 
supported the IRA. 
  The British officials have created a smokey screen whenever 
they had failed in their foreign policy, said the article adding 
that the present propaganda ploy against Tehran comes in the 
aftermath of the last month disclosure of Britain's 
eavesdropping at the Iranian Embassy in London. 

</TEXT>

