<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia, Ukraine To Deliver Ammunition, Supplies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia, Ukraine To Deliver Ammunition, Supplies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3105131994 Delhi All India Radio General Overseas Service 
in English 1000 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3105131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio General Overseas Service 
in English 1000 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India is expected to receive thousands of defense 
spare parts and critically required ammunition from Russia and 
Ukraine within three months. Addressing the naval commanders 
conference in New Delhi today, the minister of state for 
defense, Mr. Mallikarjun, said this was successfully negotiated 
during the visit of a defense delegation to the countries early 
this month. He expressed concern at the increasing belligerency 
and weapons acquisition beyond its requirements by Pakistan. 
Referring to the low intensity conflict by Pakistan to 
destabilize India, the minister lauded the efforts of Navy and 
the Coast Guard in countering seaborne operations of subversive 
elements. He stressed the need for self-reliance and 
highlighted the necessity to undertake multi-institutional 
research to build all types of vessels and sophisticated 
warships. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

