<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Congress-I Spokesman Rules Out Early Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Congress-I Spokesman Rules Out Early Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3005154694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3005154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Congress-I claims that the voter has put stamp 
of approval on the policies, programs and performance of the 
party in the just concluded by-elections. Talking to 
newspersons in New Delhi today, the party spokesman, Mr. V.N. 
Gadgil, said it is significant that five of the Lok Sabha 
constituencies, which Congress-I has won, are all rural 
constituencies and thus prove that rural people and farmers have 
rejected the opposition propaganda about Dunkel proposals. 
  Describing by-elections as trend setter, Mr. Gadgil, however 
ruled out the possibility of early general elections in the 
country. 

</TEXT>

