<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jordanian Higher Education Minister Pays Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jordanian Higher Education Minister Pays Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets al-Zu'bi, al-Shar' </H4>

<F P=102> JN3005140394 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3005140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mahmud al-Zu'bi, chairman of the Council of 
Ministers, received at 1100 today Dr. Sa'id al-Tall, deputy 
prime minister and higher education minister of the Hashemite 
Kingdom of Jordan, and the delegation accompanying him. The 
meeting was attended by Dr. Salihah Sunqur, minister of higher 
education, and the Jordanian ambassador in Damascus. 
  Dr. al-Tall conveyed Jordanian Prime Minister Dr. 
'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali's greetings to Mahmud al-Zu'bi, who also 
requested the Jordanian official to convey his greetings to Dr. 
al-Majali. 
  Talks during the meeting centered on the existing 
cooperation 
relations between the two fraternal countries. 
  Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' also received Sa'id al-Tall 
and his delegation this morning. The Jordanian ambassador in 
Damascus attended. Talks during the meeting revolved around the 
situation in the region, as well as the Arab situation, 
especially current events in fraternal Yemen. The two sides 
voiced their concern about Yemen's unity and stressed the need 
to end the bloodshed and infighting as soon as possible. 
  The two sides also tackled developments in the peace 
process, 
as well as the continuation of coordination with Syria and 
fraternal Lebanon. They then discussed relations between the 
two fraternal countries, Syria and Jordan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

