<H3> <TI>   Egyptian Petroleum Minister, Delegation Depart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egyptian Petroleum Minister, Delegation Depart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2905061294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0415 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2905061294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus--Egyptian Petroleum Minister Hamdi al-Banbi 
and his delegation left Damascus to return to Cairo last night 
following a visit of several days to Syria. The Egyptian 
minister held a number of meetings with Dr. Nadir Nabulsi, 
minister of oil and mineral resources, and senior officials from 
the ministry and companies affiliated with it. Their talks 
focused on promoting cooperation between Syria and Egypt in all 
oil areas. 
  He was seen off at Damascus International Airport by Dr. 
Nadir Nabulsi, senior ministry officials, and the Egyptian 
ambassador in Damascus. 

