<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cultural Cooperation Agreement With Cyprus Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cultural Cooperation Agreement With Cyprus Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3005161294 Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY in English 1440 GMT 
30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3005161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nicosia, May 30 (CNA) -- Cyprus and Syria have 
signed a cultural cooperation programme for a three-year period. 
  The programme was signed in Damascus by Cyprus Education and 
Culture Minister Klairi Angelidhou and her Syrian counterpart 
Muhammad Ghassan al-Halabi, during Angelidhou's official visit 
to Syria. 
  During her stay in Syria, Angelidhou had separate meetings 
with the Syrian ministers of culture and higher education, Najah 
al-'Attar and Salilah Sunqur. 
  Angelidhou was also received by Syrian Prime Minister Mahmud 
al-Zu'bi, whom she briefed on the latest developments in the 
Cyprus problem. 
  She thanked al-Zu'bi for the consistent position of the 
Syrian Government and of president Hafiz al-Asad on the Cyprus 
problem. 
  Al-Zub'i reiterated his country's support for a just 
solution 
of the Cyprus issue on the basis of U.N. Security Council 
resolutions and stressed that Syria rejected any kind of 
occupation or intervention of one country in the affairs of 
another. 
  The Northern part of the Republic of Cyprus has been under 
Turkish military occupation since 1974. 
  The Cypriot minister had also a meeting with the Greek 
Orthodox patriarch of Antioch Ignatios. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

