<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Majali Stresses Support for Palestinian Authority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Majali Stresses Support for Palestinian Authority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105161094 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1500 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3105161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali 
received at his office today Ilyas Frayj, Dr. Zakariya al-Agha, 
Dr. 'Azmi al-Shu'aybi, and Dr. 'Abd-al-Hafiz al-Ashhab, who have 
been appointed members of the Palestinian National Authority 
[PNA], as well as the Palestinian ambassador in Amman. 
  Dr. al-Majali stressed to the Palestinian delegation 
Jordan's 
firm support for the PNA in its new task in Gaza and Jericho. 
He emphasized that Jordan views coordination with the PNA as an 
indispensable need for which there is no alternative. 
  The Palestinian delegation expressed its great appreciation 
for His Majesty King Husayn and his stands, which reflect the 
sincerity of his majesty, the Jordanian political leadership, 
and the Jordanian people toward the Palestinian people. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

