<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ramadan: U.S. `Nervous Statements' Reflect Isolation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ramadan: U.S. `Nervous Statements' Reflect Isolation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105183094 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1445 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3105183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 31 May (INA)--Vice President Taha Yasin 
Ramadan has said that U.S. officials' nervous statements reflect 
U.S. isolation at the UN Security Council and the fact that U.S. 
misleading tactics have been exposed after the development of 
the stands of most UN Security Council member states and their 
calls for raising the issue of lifting the unjust blockade 
imposed on Iraq. 
  During a meeting with a delegation from the Tunisian 
commission for lifting the blockade imposed on Iraq under 
'Izz-al-Din al-Shabi, the vice president added: America's 
agents and slaves from among Arab and other rulers are suffering 
the same isolation. He stressed that the children of Arabism 
will avenge their nation and will punish those who turned Arab 
land, waters, and wealth into tools to strike at great Iraq and 
its independent revolutionary course. 
  Taha Yasin Ramadan said that the blockade will be terminated 
thanks to the will of the Iraqi people, who set an example in 
willpower, patience, jihad, and construction. He praised the 
genuine pan-Arab stands of the Arab people in Tunis and 
everywhere in the Arab world. He commended their endorsement of 
the causes that Iraq has volunteered to defend and paid immense 
sacrifices for their sake. 
  'Izz-al-Din al-Shabi praised President Saddam Husayn's brave 
leadership, which has become a beacon exposing agents and 
traitors. He stressed the free Arabs' love for Saddam Husayn 
because his excellency has become a symbol of the Arab love for 
freedom, independence, and progress and rejection subordination 
and colonialism. 

</TEXT>

