<H3> <TI>   Allied Use of Facilities Protested to Arab League </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Allied Use of Facilities Protested to Arab League </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3105135494 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1022 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3105135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 31 May (INA) -- Iraq has protested the 
facilities that are still being provided by Saudi and Kuwaiti 
rulers to American, British, and French aircraft. A letter sent 
by Iraq's permanent Arab League delegate to the League's 
secretariat noted that the facilities extended to the aircraft 
violating Iraqi airspace pose a threat to the security, 
sovereignty, and national unity of the country. 
  From 17 to 23 May, these aircraft mounted 372 sorties, 
having 
taken off from bases in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait. 
  Iraq's League delegate asked that copies of the letter, 
which 
detailed the violations, be circulated among the member states. 

</TEXT>

