BFN 

  [Excerpts] Dr. Sa'id al-Tall, Jordanian deputy prime 
minister and higher education minister, and his accompanying 
delegation arrived in Damascus via Dar'a this evening. [passage 
omitted] 
  Dr. al-Tall made a statement to a Syrian Arab News Agency 
correspondent in Dar'a. He expressed happiness at this visit, 
and said: On my visit to fraternal Syria, I would like first to 
convey to His Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad greetings from 
His Majesty King Husayn. In my name and on behalf of the 
delegation, I also convey to His Excellency President Hafiz 
al-Asad profound appreciation, respect, and pride. 
  Dr. al-Tall added: We are emphasizing a consistent fact, in 
addition to the pan-Arab ties between both fraternal countries, 
which are two parts of a whole. The two countries are facing 
the challenges posed to the Arab nation. 
