<H3> <TI>   Al-Tarifi Named Head of Civil Coordination Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Tarifi Named Head of Civil Coordination Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3105182294 Jerusalem AL-MANAR in Arabic 30 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC3105182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-MANAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinian leadership has appointed lawyer 
Jamil al-Tarifi general coordinator for the civilian authorities 
with the rank of minister and head of the Civil Coordination 
Committee, enjoying all the privileges of the National Authority 
and attending its meetings. His will have direct contact with 
President Yasir 'Arafat. 
  It is worth noting that al-Tarifi is head of the Palestinian 
team at the negotiations on civil authority and the transfer of 
privileges. He is considered to be one of the people closest to 
the PLO chairman. 
  'Arafat asked al-Tarifi to come to Tunis last week, along 
with a number of other figures, to take part in the expanded 
meetings of the Palestinian leadership. 

