<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authority Members To Arrive `Next Week' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authority Members To Arrive `Next Week' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0106100394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 1 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0106100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The first representatives of the Palestinian 
Authority will arrive in Jericho next week. This was said by 
sources in Jericho to our correspondent Moti Amir. Among those 
arriving will be Abu-al-'Ala' [Ahmad Quray'] and Nabil Sha'th. 
Meanwhile, 18 offices for the use of the Palestinian Authority 
members -- including an office for Yasir 'Arafat -- have been 
completed in Jericho. Our correspondent notes that the 
Palestinians will also set up a special office in Jericho for 
handling the intifadah victims. 
  [Earlier on the same newscast, it is noted that "the closure 
imposed on al-Ram yesterday -- after the security forces killed 
the Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] activist who has killed 
Shin Bet officer No'am Kohen -- was lifted today."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

