<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supplies, Cars for Police Cross Border at Rafah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Supplies, Cars for Police Cross Border at Rafah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2905155994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1350 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2905155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rafah, 29 May (MENA) -- Six trucks loaded with 
weapons, ammunition, other supplies, foodstuffs, tents, and 
equipment, and a number of light vehicles for the Palestinian 
police force, crossed Rafah border point this afternoon to 
reinforce the Palestinian security forces in the self-rule 
regions. 
  Major General 'Abd-al-Razzaq al-Mahayidah, commander of the 
Palestinian forces in Rafah, said 250 Palestinian policemen 
coming from Algeria are due to enter Rafah tomorrow, Monday. 
  He said negotiations will be held with Israel on the Rafah 
and Jericho crossing points with a view to completing technical 
preparations there before handing them over to the Palestinian 
National Authority. 

</TEXT>

