has submitted an official application to obtain a permanent seat 
at the UN Security Council. 
  In a statement made today on the sidelines of the 
Non-Aligned 
Movement Conference, al-'Arabi said that the African group has 
also requested two permanent seats on the council. 
  He explained that the UN General Assembly is expected to 
consider the expansion of the UN Security Council membership and 
including other countries at its session next year. 

