<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   11th Conference of Non-Aligned Countries Resumes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    11th Conference of Non-Aligned Countries Resumes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Musa Explains Serbia's Absence </H4>

<F P=102> NC0106193394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1855 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (MENA) -- [Egyptian] Foreign Minister 
'Amr Musa has explained that Serbia was not invited to the 
Non-Aligned Movement [NAM] foreign ministers conference in 
accordance with an agreement between the Movement's chairman, 
Indonesia, and Egypt. He noted that this issue had not been 
raised by any member, either during general meetings or at 
committee meetings or consultations. 
  Musa was replying to a question by a MENA correspondent on 
why Serbia was not invited. He said: As chairman of the NAM 
foreign ministers conference, Egypt is bound by the measures 
decided upon in the New York coordination office and during 
consultations in Jakarta and agreed upon by NAM members. 
According to these measures, Serbia will not attend NAM 
meetings unless a matter relating to its own entity is being 
discussed, Musa explained. Only in such a case can Serbia be 
invited to give its opinion on the matter, he said. 
  Musa affirmed that there is a consensus on banning Serbia's 
and Montenegro's participation in NAM meetings. 

</TEXT>

