<H4>    Pakistani Minister Views Kashmir Issue </H4>

<F P=102> BK0106162594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0106162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Pakistani] Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali 
has told the Non-Aligned Movement [NAM] ministerial meeting in 
Cairo that the Kashmiri people's right to self-determination is 
an acclaimed, undeniable, and irreversible truth and should not 
be subjected to political expediency. 
  Addressing the meeting, the foreign minister stressed that 
the process of self-determination must be completed by granting 
the right of self-determination to the people of Jammu and 
Kashmir, who are engaged in a relentless struggle against Indian 
oppression. He said the cruelty that has been adopted to crush 
the Kashmiri people's struggle is unparalleled in history. The 
official machinery and institutions in occupied Kashmir have a 
free hand to commit all sorts of atrocities to suppress the 
people's aspirations. Torture, the molestation of women, the 
death of people in detention, robbery, and the burning of 
people's houses have become routine. These cruel activities are 
being committed by the more than 500,000 occupation forces 
deployed in occupied Kashmir. 
  The foreign minister also told the Non-Aligned Movement 
ministerial meeting that massive attempts are being made to 
misrepresent the indigenous uprising launched by the people of 
Kashmir. Allegations are being made about foreign interference 
and assistance in this regard. He reminded India that the light 
of freedom has never been extinguished by oppression and terror. 
He said this misleading and cruel policy is no answer to the 
situation in occupied Kashmir. The only solution to the Kashmir 
issue is to implement the UN Security Council resolution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

