<H4>    Indian Minister Criticizes Pakistan </H4>

<F P=102> BK0206041494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0206041494 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India has criticized Pakistan for raising the 
Kashmir issue at the Non-Aligned Foreign Minister's meeting, 
saying the movement cannot be involved in the matter. The 
minister of state for external affairs, Mr. R.L. Bhatia, told 
the meeting in Cairo that New Delhi has always been ready for 
the dialogue with Pakistan on the Kashmir issue but there has 
been little response from Islamabad. In a strongly worded 
response to a Pakistani demand for intervention by NAM 
[Non-Aligned Movement] in the issue, Mr. Bhatia said: Pakistan 
is inflicting enormous suffering on the people of New Delhi 
through state sponsored terrorism. He asserted that Kashmir is 
and will always remain an integral part of India. 
  Mr. Bhatia reminded the meeting of the ruling by the NAM 
chairman Indonesia that bilateral disputes should not be 
discussed at the NAM meeting. He said: Any moves going against 
the ruling can only weaken the movement. 

</TEXT>

