<H4>    Iraqi-Kuwaiti Altercation Over Embargo </H4>

<F P=102> NC0106192094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1735 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (MENA) -- MENA has learned that the 
meeting of the political committee of the 11th conference of the 
Non-Aligned Movement [NAM] of foreign ministers, currently being 
held in Cairo, has witnessed an altercation for the second time 
between the Iraqi and Kuwaiti foreign ministers. The Iraqi 
minister requested the conference issue a decision to lift the 
economic embargo on Iraq, and the Kuwaiti minister objected to 
that request. 
  MENA has also learned that a number of participants 
requested 
that the Iraqi people's suffering be curbed and demanded that 
the conference issue a recommendation to that effect. 

</TEXT>

