<H4>    Government Mediates Between Iraq, Kuwait </H4>

<F P=102> NC0106204894 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2000 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0106204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our correspondent has learned that Egypt, in its 
capacity as chairman of the Non-Aligned Movement [NAM] 
conference, is currently working to bring the views of Iraq and 
Kuwait closer on the final statement of the conference, which 
will be issued Friday [3 June]. The draft Egypt prepared is 
based on Iraq's recognition of Kuwait, its sovereignty, its 
safety, and its regional border. The draft also notes progress 
in Iraq's position and the need to consider the suffering of the 
Iraqi people. 

